<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The function OS_ModuleGetInfo_Impl is a no-op stub: it does not use its parameters, has no side effects, and simply returns the constant OS_SUCCESS. The call OS_ModuleGetInfo_Impl(&token, module_prop) in OS_ModuleInfo therefore executes but does nothing that affects program behaviour (removing the call or replacing it with return_code = OS_SUCCESS would not change behaviour). This constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
